Frequently Asked Questions about Studying at Charles University Faculty of Medicine in Hradec Kralove
What programs does the Charles University Faculty of Medicine in Hradec Kralove offer? The Faculty of Medicine offers a wide range of programs, including undergraduate degrees in medicine, dentistry, pharmacy, and public health, as well as postgraduate and doctoral programs in various medical specialties.
What is the admission process like for international students? The admission process for international students varies depending on the program and level of study. Generally, applicants are required to submit academic transcripts, standardized test scores (such as the MCAT or equivalent), letters of recommendation, and a personal statement. Proficiency in English or Czech may also be required, depending on the language of instruction.
What is student life like in Hradec Kralove? Hradec Kralove offers a vibrant student life with numerous cultural, social, and recreational activities. Students can explore the city's historic landmarks, attend cultural events, and participate in clubs and organizations on campus. The city also has a lively nightlife scene with restaurants, cafes, and bars.
